			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">For getting the DC horse into the first castle and into the 2nd field to the tables I do this:
<br />

<br />
1.  Get a Fire Resist buff if ones around (Helps reduce lava dmg)
<br />

<br />
2.  Tag DC horse with slow and CoS invis
<br />

<br />
3.  Bring it to the Jopal Island (slowly especially if you have your run5)
<br />

<br />
4.  Wait till it starts beating on you at the Jopal Island and reslow it
<br />

<br />
5.  I refresh my Rune and then cast Night's Beckon on it and finally CoS invis
<br />

<br />
6.  I then run to the back of the Jopal tent that has the lava tunnel and wait till I see the horse enter.  As soon as it enters I start swiming the tunnel.
<br />

<br />
7.  I pop up towards the back of the lava tunnel and just lev right above the lava, pop up front and you'll get agro from a couple mobs.
<br />

<br />
8.  I wait till the DC horse is hitting on me then make the DA run through the tunnel.  (Helps me a ton to look at the ceiling, all the agro spam causes me some lag which can turn me around when running)
<br />

<br />
9.  The key for letting the horse catch up for me is to use the first DA and as soon as I click open the door and start my run out into the castle area I click off the DA Click CoS invis.  Once past the first two guards use the next DA and just stand there for 8-10 seconds.  This gives the horse time to catch up.  (I make sure to keep the horse on target, pain in the butt trying to target it once it's off and your kiting half the castle)
<br />

<br />
10.  After that it's just a matter of getting enough distance to snare the horse and either FDing, evacing or Dieing.  Helps a ton to have dot extension, to pass that 2 minute mark.
<br />

<br />
note...If you die but get the horse snared run back to the castle, and catch it before it waunders back.  When I first started trying I ended up doing it this way a ton.  Also, there's a ton of casters usually in there so once I snare the horse I run up one of the two stairs cases and fd there, out of caster LOS.
<br />

<br />
11.  Lastly, if the birds are up you'll have to walk the horse letting it beat on you pretty much the whole time till it's past them.  I use the right side and just really slowly walk it past while high on the side of the wall, if you get too far it'll path down the cliff and agro a bird.
<br />

<br />

<br />
This is just the way I do it, there are probably better ways out there.  I grinded about 900 aa's at the tables with those horses.  Only sucky part of the DC horses is when someone pulls a caster through you and it ends up dispelling your pet.  Other than that it's easy to hold down 11 guards solo before respawn.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Hope this helps,
<br />
Aumudn of Friona Vie</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
